# Plan — Queue basado en BD para assistant-worker

## Problema a resolver

El raw `Redis::lpush / brPop` entre PHP y el Node worker no tiene acknowledgment.
Si el worker cae después del `brPop` pero antes de terminar, el job desaparece sin retries ni notificación.

---

## Diseño de la solución

Reemplazar el lpush/brPop con una tabla `assistant_jobs` en BD.
Node hace polling con `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` cada 500ms vía un endpoint interno de Laravel.

```
SendMessage → ProcessAssistantMessage (Laravel Queue) → INSERT assistant_jobs
                                                             ↓
                                              Node: POST /jobs/claim (polling 500ms)
                                                             ↓
                                              Node: ConversationWorker.process()
                                                             ↓
                                     éxito → POST /jobs/:id/complete
                                     fallo → POST /jobs/:id/fail (retry con backoff)
                                                             ↓
                                     attempts >= max → status=failed + WS AssistantError
                                                             ↓
                              SweepStuckJobs (cada minuto) → reclaima jobs stuck > 2min
```

---

## Esquema de la tabla

```sql
CREATE TABLE assistant_jobs (
  id               BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  conversation_id  BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES assistant_conversations(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  message_id       BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES assistant_messages(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id          BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  request_id       VARCHAR(255),
  status           VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',   -- pending|processing|done|failed
  attempts         SMALLINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  max_attempts     SMALLINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,
  claimed_at       TIMESTAMP,
  error            TEXT,
  available_at     TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
  created_at       TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),

  INDEX (status, available_at),   -- query de claim
  INDEX (status, claimed_at)      -- query del sweep
)
```

**Nota clave**: FK a `assistant_conversations` (no `conversations`) y a `assistant_messages`.

Backoff exponencial: `available_at = NOW() + 30 * 2^(attempts-1) segundos`
- Intento 1 falla → espera 30s
- Intento 2 falla → espera 60s
- Intento 3 falla → status=failed

