## Archivos a modificar

### PHP — `ProcessAssistantMessage.php`
Reemplazar el bloque `Redis::connection('pubsub')->lpush(...)` por:
```php
AssistantJob::create([
    'conversation_id' => $this->conversationId,
    'message_id'      => $this->messageId,
    'user_id'         => $this->userId,
    'request_id'      => Context::get('request_id'),
    'status'          => 'pending',
    'available_at'    => now(),
]);
```
Eliminar `use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Redis;`.
Renombrar log a `assistant.job_created`.

### PHP — `routes/assistant-internal.php`
Añadir dentro del grupo `assistant.service`:
```php
Route::post('jobs/claim',            ClaimJobController::class);
Route::post('jobs/{jobId}/complete', CompleteJobController::class);
Route::post('jobs/{jobId}/fail',     FailJobController::class);
```

### PHP — `routes/console.php`
Añadir:
```php
Schedule::job(SweepStuckJobs::class)->everyMinute()->withoutOverlapping();
```

### Node — `services/assistant-worker/src/api/LaravelClient.ts`
El método `request()` hace `res.json()` incondicionalmente. Hay que manejar body vacío:
```ts
const text = await res.text()
return text ? JSON.parse(text) : { data: null }
```

### Node — `services/assistant-worker/src/index.ts`
Eliminar: import de `redis`, `createClient`, conexión Redis, loop `brPop`.
Añadir: `AssistantJobPoller`, señales `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` para graceful shutdown.

